{"parse":{"title":"Why I'm No Longer Talking to White People About Race","pageid":55132008,"revid":849263564,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Why I\u2019m No Longer Talking to White People About Race <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Why+I%E2%80%99m+No+Longer+Talking+to+White+People+About+Race&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BReni+Eddo-Lodge%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BBloomsbury+Publishing%5D%5D\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Why_I%27m_no_longer_talking_to_white_people_about_race.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Why I&#39;m no longer talking to white people about race.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Why_I%27m_no_longer_talking_to_white_people_about_race.jpg/220px-Why_I%27m_no_longer_talking_to_white_people_about_race.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"353\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f2/Why_I%27m_no_longer_talking_to_white_people_about_race.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"249\" data-file-height=\"399\" /></a><div>Cover</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Reni_Eddo-Lodge\" title=\"Reni Eddo-Lodge\">Reni Eddo-Lodge</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/United_Kingdom\" title=\"United Kingdom\">United Kingdom</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Subjects</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Race_(human_categorization)\" title=\"Race (human categorization)\">Race</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Racism\" title=\"Racism\">racism</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/White_privilege\" title=\"White privilege\">white privilege</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Feminism\" title=\"Feminism\">feminism</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Published</th><td>\nJune 1, 2017</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Bloomsbury_Publishing\" title=\"Bloomsbury Publishing\">Bloomsbury Publishing</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/E-book\" title=\"E-book\">E-book</a>, print</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-4088-7056-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-4088-7056-3\">978-1-4088-7056-3</a> paperback</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Why I\u2019m No Longer Talking to White People About Race</b></i> is a 2017 polemic debut book by writer <a href=\"/wiki/Reni_Eddo-Lodge\" title=\"Reni Eddo-Lodge\">Reni Eddo-Lodge</a> that was released by <a href=\"/wiki/Bloomsbury_Publishing\" title=\"Bloomsbury Publishing\">Bloomsbury Publishing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Bloomsbury_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Bloomsbury-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Grant_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Grant-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The 2015 <a href=\"/wiki/Booker_Prize\" title=\"Booker Prize\">Booker Prize</a>-winner <a href=\"/wiki/Marlon_James_(novelist)\" title=\"Marlon James (novelist)\">Marlon James</a> wrote that it was \"essential\" and \"begging to be written\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Bloomsbury_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Bloomsbury-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reviews\">Reviews</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Why_I%27m_No_Longer_Talking_to_White_People_About_Race&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Reviews\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Trevor_Phillips\" title=\"Trevor Phillips\">Trevor Phillips</a> reviewed the work for <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Times\" title=\"The Times\">The Times</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\nIn the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Times_Literary_Supplement\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Times Literary Supplement\">Times Literary Supplement</a></i>, Bernadine Evaristo described the book's title as \"gloriously provocative\", noting that it was \"marketing gold\" in the climate surrounding the <a href=\"/wiki/Black_Lives_Matter\" title=\"Black Lives Matter\">Black Lives Matter</a> movement. Evaristo described the work as \"timely and accessible\", \"comprehensive and journalistic\" as well as \"resolutely unacademic\", comparing it to the work of African-American writer <a href=\"/wiki/Roxane_Gay\" title=\"Roxane Gay\">Roxane Gay</a>, whose 2014 anthology <i><a href=\"/wiki/Bad_Feminist\" title=\"Bad Feminist\">Bad Feminist</a></i> \"treads some of the same ground\". However, she critiques Eddo-Lodge for not engaging in enough \"rigorous research, particularly into the past\" and for the fact that she \"completely overlooks\" the work of Black British feminist writers like Beverley Bryan, Stella Dadzie and Suzanne Scafe. Evaristo also noted that the book leaves open further questions, such as \"What is the responsibility of black people in creating change for ourselves? Without also taking responsibility, we are dependent and powerless. What about the numerous positive developments since <a href=\"/wiki/HMT_Empire_Windrush#West_Indian_immigrants\" title=\"HMT Empire Windrush\">\n<i>Windrush</i></a><i>?\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> </i>\n</p><p>Arifa Akbar reviewed the work for the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Financial_Times\" title=\"Financial Times\">Financial Times</a></i>, noting that Eddo-Lodge \"builds on a critical tradition drawn from black American writers\" like <a href=\"/wiki/W._E._B._Du_Bois\" title=\"W. E. B. Du Bois\">W. E. B. Du Bois</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/James_Baldwin\" title=\"James Baldwin\">James Baldwin</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Bell_hooks\" title=\"Bell hooks\">bell hooks</a>. Akbar notes that \"Not everyone will find the answer to racial inequality in Eddo-Lodge's reliance on white consciousness-raising, but it is an important shift that undermines the idea that racism is the BAME community's burden to carry. The liberation that this book offers is in the reversal of responsibilities.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Writing for <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Guardian\" title=\"The Guardian\">The Guardian</a></i>, <a href=\"/wiki/Colin_Grant_(author)\" title=\"Colin Grant (author)\">Colin Grant</a> places the book within a wider tradition of \"angry warnings to an ignorant white readership\", the majority of which have been produced by African-American rather than Black British writers. Grant opined that \"Eddo-Lodge accurately takes the temperature of racial discussions in the UK\" but that several sections, such as its discussion of the murder of Stephen Lawrence, are too brief, stating that \"this kind of book is not designed to delve beyond the headlines in order to draw lessons from the past\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Grant_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Grant-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Reviewing the work for <a href=\"/wiki/NPR\" title=\"NPR\">NPR</a>, the journalist Silvia Vi\u00f1as stated that the work's \"boldness\" and \"straight talk\" is what makes it \"memorable\", also noting that while focusing \"on events in Britain, it's still accessible to readers of black American history.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Why_I%27m_No_Longer_Talking_to_White_People_About_Race&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Bloomsbury-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Bloomsbury_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Bloomsbury_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Eddo-Lodge, Reni. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.bloomsbury.com/uk/why-im-no-longer-talking-to-white-people-about-race-9781408870570/\"><i>Why I\u2019m No Longer Talking to White People About Race</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Bloomsbury_Publishing\" title=\"Bloomsbury Publishing\">Bloomsbury Publishing</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">30 April</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Why+I%E2%80%99m+No+Longer+Talking+to+White+People+About+Race&amp;rft.pub=Bloomsbury+Publishing&amp;rft.au=Eddo-Lodge%2C+Reni&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomsbury.com%2Fuk%2Fwhy-im-no-longer-talking-to-white-people-about-race-9781408870570%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWhy+I%27m+No+Longer+Talking+to+White+People+About+Race\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Grant-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Grant_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Grant_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Grant, Colin (3 June 2017). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/books/2017/jun/03/why-no-long-talking-white-people-review-race-